        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Designates June 14, 2004, as National Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag Day.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>82</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-06-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-09-03T15:10:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary has been expanded because action occurred on the measure.)</b></p> <p>States that the Senate: (1) supports and reveres the U.S. flag and the Pledge of Allegiance; (2) strongly disapproves of the decision by the three-judge panel of the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit in Newdow v. United States Congress; and (3) designates June 14, 2004, as National Pledge of Allegiance to the Flag Day.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
